value.0: The bright, healthy green leaves and stems of this fern shift slighty in the breeze.
These are the berries made by the danberry bush.
This is a beautiful, gentle flower.
This is a beautiful, gentle flower.

Cori May was a sweet natured fey,
Until a very disturbing day,
When all grew dark, and the great lord did frown,
And with a callous gesture did set her down.
But from the grave she still gives power,
And all it costs is a single flower.

The white side of Dan was kind and cheery,
But the dark side did sometimes make him dreary,
And when t'was determined a mistake he made,
Into this coffin his corpse was laid.
As his spirit still here tarries,
Do be kind and bring him berries.
